									<RECORD id="0-0-0-48031" number="61000" version="3">
										<HEADING>§ 26-1901 City-owned vacant property under the jurisdiction of the department of housing preservation and development that may be suitable for the development of affordable housing.</HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-11745" name="26-1901"/>§ 26-1901 City-owned vacant property under the jurisdiction of the department of housing preservation and development that may be suitable for the development of affordable housing.</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-48032" number="61001" version="3">
											<PARA>By no later than November 1, 2018, and by November 1 of each year thereafter, the department of housing preservation and development shall, with the cooperation of all other appropriate agencies, report to the mayor and the speaker of the council the following information disaggregated by council district: a report of vacant buildings or lots under the jurisdiction of the department categorized according to the potential development or feasibility status of such buildings or lots as affordable housing.</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-48033" number="61002" version="3">
											<PARA>(L.L. 2018/030, 1/8/2018, eff. 7/7/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-021]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
